    "Convex Optimization in 3DConvex optimization techniques have been increasingly adopted in recent years for 3D reconstruction and scene representation tasks.",
    "[18] introduced CVXNet, a framework that reconstructs 3D objects from input images by decomposing them into a collection of convex primitives.",
    "Each primitive is represented as a convex hull, allowing the network to generate a polygonal mesh composed of multiple convex polytopes with well-defined geometric boundaries."
